.TH "sprd_mcdt_chan_write" 9 "sprd_mcdt_chan_write" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sprd_mcdt_chan_write \- write data to the MCDT channel's fifo
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" sprd_mcdt_chan_write
.BI "(struct sprd_mcdt_chan *chan "  ","
.BI "char *tx_buf "  ","
.BI "u32 size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "chan" 12
the MCDT channel
.IP "tx_buf" 12
send buffer
.IP "size" 12
data size
.SH "NOTE"
We can not write data to the channel fifo when enabling the DMA mode,
otherwise the channel fifo data will be invalid.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If there are not enough space of the channel fifo, it will return errors
to users.

Returns 0 on success, or an appropriate error code on failure.
